    "subType": "spell",
    "description": "<p>The elementalist chooses earth, water, fire, or wind when casting this spell and selects a visible target to be affected. For the rest of the scene, the target is immune to injury caused by mundane manifestations of that substance; stone weapons don&rsquo;t harm them, water doesn&rsquo;t drown them, fire doesn&rsquo;t burn them, and wind doesn&rsquo;t topple them. This affects secondary effects of the material as well; a fire-pacted mage couldn&rsquo;t be boiled in a pot, and an earth-pacted one won&rsquo;t be suffocated if buried alive.&nbsp;</p>",
